o drugs and alcohol, and his profuse domestic violence, has buckled under the strain of Sharon gaining a public profile. The moral of the story seems to be that being beaten by your out-of-control husband shouldn't be tolerated in the first place, because it might be a sign that your partner doesn't have your best&nbsp;interests&nbsp;at heart. Who knew?</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/sharon-osbourne\">Sharon Osbourne</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/ozzyosbourne\">Ozzy Osbourne</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/popandrock\">Pop and rock</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/society/drugs\">Drugs</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/society/alcohol\">Alcohol</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/society/domestic-violence\">Domestic violence</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/the-x-factor\">The X Factor</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/entertainment\">Entertainment</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/music/blacksabbath\">Black Sabbath</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/culture/television\">Television</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/deborah-orr\">Deborah Orr</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" />" "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/2013/apr/20/sharon-ozzy-osbourne-separation-rumours" (20851 1365) old 18 nil nil ((title nil "Sharon and Ozzy Osbourne's separation rumours are no surprise") (link nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/2013/apr/20/sharon-ozzy-osbourne-separation-rumours") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/64354?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Asharon-ozzy-osbourne-separation-rumours%3A1896519&ch=Television+%26amp%3B+radio&c3=Guardian&c4=Sharon+Osbourne%2COzzy+Osbourne%2CMusic%2CPop+and+rock+%28Music+genre%29%2CDrugs+illegal+%28Society%29%2CSociety%2CAlcohol+%28Society%29%2CDomestic+violence+%28Society%29%2CX+Factor+%28TV+and+radio%29%2CEntertainment+%28TV+genre%29%2CBlack+Sabbath%2CTelevision+%28Culture%29%2CTelevision+and+radio+TV%2CCulture&c5=Society+Weekly%2CFolk+Rock+Music%2CPop+Music%2CNot+commercially+useful%2CSocial+Care+Society%2CCommunities+Society%2CTelevision+Media%2CTV&c6=Deborah+Orr&c7=2013%2F04%2F20+10%3A15&c8=1896519&c9=Article&c10=Feature&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Sharon+and+Ozzy+Osbourne%27s+separation+rumours+are+no+surprise&c66=Culture&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FCulture%2FTelevision+%26amp%3B+radio%2FSharon+Osbourne\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">Drugs, alcohol and domestic violence tend not to make a happy marriage. Add to that Sharon's success, and who would have guessed the outcome?</p><p>Ozzy and Sharon Osbourne are rumoured to have ended their marriage after 31 years. Apparently, a union that has survived Ozzy's addiction to drugs and alcohol, and his profuse domestic violence, has buckled under the strain of Sharon gaining a public profile. The moral of the story seems to be that being beaten by your out-of-control husband shouldn't be tolerated in the first place, because it might be a sign that your partner doesn't have your best&nbsp;interests&nbsp;at heart. Who knew?</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/tv-and-radio/sharon-osbourne\">Sharon Osbourne</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/